<glossary>
<definition id="fs-id1171240253588">
<term>displacement current</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171240251462">extra term in Maxwell’s equations that is analogous to a real current but accounts for a changing electric field producing a magnetic field, even when the real current is present</meaning>
</definition>
<definition id="fs-id1171240251470">
<term>Maxwell’s equations</term>
<meaning id="fs-id1171240251476">set of four equations that comprise a complete, overarching theory of electromagnetism</meaning>
</definition>
</glossary>
